{"title":"New Sage Titanium Storm King GP gravel bike springs up w/ suspension-ready geometry","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/10/06/new-sage-titanium-storm-king-gp-gravel-bike-charges-out-w-suspension-ready-geo/","date":1633521652000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"sage storm king gp titanium gravel bike with front suspension\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121635/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-0.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-273485\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Built off their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/11/13/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-reigns-like-an-adventure-monster/\">original Storm King</a> “Monster Gravel” bike, the new Storm King GP gets suspension corrected geometry tailor-made for running the new Rockshox Rudy gravel fork.</p><p>Add in the rest of that <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/10/sram-xplr-gravel-group-debuts-rockshox-fork-dropper-wide-gearing-moto-wheels/\">new SRAM XPLR package</a>, including the 1x SRAM drivetrain and Zipp Moto XPLR wheels, and they’ll calling it the bike to take on any road, anywhere, anytime…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7.jpg\" alt=\"sage storm king gp titanium gravel bike with front suspension\" width=\"1000\" height=\"1500\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7.jpg 1000w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121652/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-7-768x1152.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\"></a></p><p>The main difference is the geometry, namely a 5mm shorter head tube to accommodate the increased axle-to-crown height of the Rudy suspension fork.</p><p>They also made the head angle slightly slacker, by half a degree, which works with the overall change in axle-to-crown height and slacker front end.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2.jpg\" alt=\"rockshox rudy gravel suspension fork on new sage storm king ti bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121640/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The standard Storm King has a 395mm A-to-C on the fork, but the 40mm travel Rockshox Rudy is 435mm. Subtract the 5mm headtube shortening, and you still have a 35mm difference. But they tweaked everything else to keep the BB drop and overall rider position the same, with handling that’s targeted at the more aggressive riding you can do with the addition of suspension.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121632/sage-storm-king-gravel-bike-geometry-chart.gif\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121632/sage-storm-king-gravel-bike-geometry-chart.gif\" alt=\"titanium sage storm king gravel bike geometry chart\" width=\"943\" height=\"605\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121649/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The seat tube is 2.25º steeper, but they’re spec’ing a 0mm offset (aka “straight”) Rockshox <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/08/10/sram-xplr-gravel-group-debuts-rockshox-fork-dropper-wide-gearing-moto-wheels/\">Reverb XPLR dropper seatpost</a>. The combination keeps the rider where they need to be in relation to the pedals, along with the…</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121643/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121646/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>…longer Front Center measurement, which was was increased by 10mm to reduce the likelihood of toe overlap with the front tire. That works with the slacker head angle to keep the Reach measurement in a similar position as the regular Storm King.</p><p>This, plus 5mm long chainstays, extend the wheelbase by about 20mm total (size 58), which should add stability at speed or when loaded down with frame bags.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121654/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-8-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>The bike gets a third bottle mount under the downtube, and a single accessory (likely for a mini fender) mount just behind the headtube (visible in fork detail photo earlier in this post).</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1400\" height=\"933\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1.jpg 1400w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121638/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-1-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1400px) 100vw, 1400px\"></a></p><p>This one is shown without top tube bag mounts…but only because the logo is there. If you want them, they can add them for no extra charge.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121657/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10.jpg\" alt=\"frame details on titanium sage storm king gravel bike\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/04121700/sage-storm-king-titanium-gravel-bike-10-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Like all of Sage Titanium’s bikes, they’re handmade in the USA. The Storm King GP will be available in a single spec, using the full SRAM Red XPLR group with dropper post and fork, Zipp Moto XPLR wheels with 40mm Zipp tires, Zipp XPLR/Service Course bar and stem, and Chris King headset and T47 bottom bracket.</p><p>MSRP is $11,765 for a non-anodized frame, and $12,765 for something like you see here with colored anodization. Custom finishes, paint, polishing, and even Cerakote, are all available for an additional charge.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=ale&amp;pw=147535&amp;mi=18629&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsagetitanium.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc\"><em>SageTitanium.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a5a3184c54a024009eebaf355916059ffac6a1e817512449e331e6712a2e8e8e","category":"Cycling"}